<section class="section" id="sec-mttk">
  <h2 class="section-title">Mean-Time-to-KEV</h2>
  <p class="section-desc">Average days between a vulnerability's public disclosure and its confirmed active exploitation — shorter means less warning time for defenders.</p>
  <div class="chart-row">
    {% if mttk.sample_size > 0 %}
    {% if mttk.gauge_svg %}
    <div class="chart-card" style="flex: 0 0 auto;">
      <p class="chart-card-title">Median lag (color zones: &lt;7d / 7-30d / &gt;30d)</p>
      {{ mttk.gauge_svg | safe }}
    </div>
    {% endif %}
    <div class="mttk-kpi-column">
      <div class="kpi-card">
        <div class="value">{{ mttk.average_days if mttk.average_days is not none else "N/A" }}</div>
        <div class="label">Average (days)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="kpi-card">
        <div class="value">{{ mttk.median_days if mttk.median_days is not none else "N/A" }}</div>
        <div class="label">Median (days)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="kpi-card">
        <div class="value">{{ mttk.sample_size }}</div>
        <div class="label">Sample size</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endif %}
    <div class="kpi-card mttk-remediation-card">
      <div class="value">{{ mttk.remediation_window_days if mttk.remediation_window_days is not none else "N/A" }}</div>
      <div class="label">CISA remediation window (avg days)</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  {% if mttk.sample_size == 0 %}
  <p class="section-desc" style="font-style: italic; margin-top: 10px;">Not enough data yet to measure disclosure-to-exploitation lag — no CVE this run was both newly critical and newly added to CISA's KEV list with a matching disclosure date. The card above still reflects CISA's own remediation deadline for this week's KEV additions, independent of that overlap.</p>
  {% endif %}
</section>
